             EDWARDS. I am a shopman to Mr. John Sowerby, of Brick-lane - he is a <rs id="t18300527-115-viclabel616" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300527-115-victim1004 t18300527-115-viclabel616"></join>. Mr. Sutton came to me on the 29th of April, and brought a handkerchief, which he asked if I knew - I said yes it was my master's, and had our mark which I had put on it; I had seen it an hour and a half or two hours before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-115-person1006">
                  MARTIN 
                  SUTTON
               <interp inst="t18300527-115-person1006" type="surname" value="SUTTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-115-person1006" type="given" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300527-115-person1006" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shopman to a pawnbroker. The prisoner brought this handkerchief to our shop, which is two hundred or three hundred yards from the prosecutor's - I stopped him on suspicion, as I had seen him attempt to steal a waistcoat from our shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300527-115-person1007">
                  JOHN 
                  WEBB
               <interp inst="t18300527-115-person1007" type="surname" value="WEBB"></interp>
